      "base": "main",
      "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds an ESLint-based linting setup to enforce code quality standards in CI for pull requests and pushes to the main branch.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added `.eslintrc.json` with ESLint recommended rules and project linting standards.\n- Added `.github/workflows/lint.yml` to run ESLint in GitHub Actions using Node.js 18.\n- Added `src/example.js` with intentional linting errors to demonstrate that the workflow fails when lint violations are present.\n\n## Testing\n\nOpen or update this pull request to trigger the Code Linting workflow. The workflow installs dependencies with `npm ci`, installs ESLint v8 globally, and runs ESLint against JavaScript files in `src/` directories. This PR intentionally includes linting errors to demonstrate the workflow; after fixing `src/example.js`, the workflow should pass.",
